              filterTo,
              filterReadingTypes = Set.empty, // filtering out of scope for this test
              filterServiceTypes = Set.empty, // typically not asked for
              filterTransportTypes = Set.empty, // filtering out of scope for this test
              filterEndOfMonth = false,
              anyDayReplacement = false,
              onlyLatest = true,
              filterInstalled = false
            )
            // The test setup is mainly designed to test the ANY algorithm and thus creates "expected" and "other"
            // readings. For the onlyLatest test without anyDayReplacement, the reading with highest consumptionDate
            // shall be returned, even if that is from a test setup point of view an "other" reading.
            // The primary key for inserting the readings to the readings database table contains
            // (meterport, consumption date (in the readings table called reading_date), readings type), while
            // for the test setup we only use a single meterport, thus the (consumptionDate, readingType) build the
            // unique key which decides if a new reading is inserted to the table or a previous reading is updated.
            // During setup of the to-be-inserted readings it is guaranteed that each reading has its own date/time,
            // and thus no reading will overwrite another reading, even if both have the same reading type.
            // Therefore, there is exactly one reading with the highest date/time, and this is expected to be returned.
            val expectedReading = scenariosWithReadingInputs
              .flatMap { case (_, expectedReadings, otherReadings) => expectedReadings ++ otherReadings }
